{"type":"message","id":"357dabe2","parentId":"9d7aab55","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:29:36.244Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_rphcp4wkfawj_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 112717\n\n## Applied Mutations\nNo mutations applied this cycle.\nRejected: a (missing)\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine what concrete action to take.\r\n\r\nCurrent status:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 are complete\r\n- CFI Analysis is done - found that 44.8% of frequency-invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Pending: CFI-weighted compression experiment\r\n\r\nThe key insight is that frequency-based compression mostly loses signal (mean CFI=0.181), and there's a distinction between:\r\n1. Process artifacts (CFI=0, metaprogramming noise)\r\n2. Research trajectory (CFI>0.7, true causal signals)\r\n\r\nThe next logical step is to implement the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Computing CFI for each invariant\r\n2. Weighting compression by CFI score\r\n3. Comparing prediction quality vs frequency baseline\r\n\r\nLet me look at what files exist that I could work with. The research/CFI_RESULTS.md contains the analysis. I need to design and implement an experiment.\r\n\r\nFor a concrete action, I should:\r\n1. Create an experiment script or modify existing code to test CFI-weighted compression\r\n2. Or update the CFI_RESULTS.md with the next experimental design\r\n\r\nActually, looking at the iteration economics - each pulse takes 30-35s. I should make a concrete file edit that advances toward the CFI-weighted compression experiment.\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment design document or start implementing the CFI-weighted compression logic. Since I need to be specific and advance goals, I'll create a new file for the experiment design or modify the CFI_RESULTS.md to include next steps.\r\n\r\nI'll update the research/CFI_RESULTS.md to add an experiment protocol for CFI-weighted compression testing.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis revealed that 94.3% of frequency-invariants have low CFI (<0.7), indicating frequency-based compression loses most signal. The next step is to implement a CFI-weighted compression experiment to test if preserving high-CFI invariants improves next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nUpdate `research/CFI_RESULTS.md` with a concrete experiment protocol for CFI-weighted compression, including the algorithm design and evaluation methodology.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: **Next:** CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n- CFI provides orthogonal signal to frequency (not a refinement)\r\n- Two types of persistence require different handling\r\n- Frequency-based compression treats both identically → loses research signal\r\n- CFI-weighted compression should preserve \"research trajectory\" invariants\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- Breakaway is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\r\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\r\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\r\n```\r\n\r\nnew_text: **Next:** CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\r\n\r\n## CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment Protocol\r\n\r\n### Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will outperform frequency-only compression because it preserves causal (high-CFI) invariants while filtering process artifacts (CFI=0).\r\n\r\n### Algorithm: CFI-Weighted Temporal Hashing\r\n\r\n```\r\nFor each token at position i:\r\n  1. Compute frequency[i] = count(token) / total_tokens\r\n  2. Compute CFI[i] = consistency_across_pulses(token)\r\n  3. Compute combined_score = CFI[i] * frequency[i]^α\r\n  \r\n  Compression decision:\r\n  - Keep if combined_score > threshold\r\n  - OR keep if CFI[i] >= 0.7 (research trajectory invariant)\r\n  - Discard otherwise\r\n```\r\n\r\nParameters:\r\n- α = 0.5 (frequency exponent, downweights frequent process terms)\r\n- threshold = 0.001 (minimal retention threshold)\r\n\r\n### Baseline Comparison\r\n| Method | Keep Criterion | Expected Behavior |\r\n|--------|----------------|-------------------|\r\n| Frequency-only | freq > 0.01 | Keeps frequent process terms, drops rare research signals |\r\n| CFI-weighted | CFI*freq^0.5 > 0.001 | Downweights process noise, preserves research causalities |\r\n| CFI-hard | CFI >= 0.7 | Aggressive filter, only true invariants |\r\n\r\n### Evaluation Metric\r\nNext-pulse prediction accuracy on held-out pulse subset:\r\n- Input: compressed state hash from pulse N\r\n- Output: reconstruction quality of pulse N+1\r\n\r\n### Experiment Files\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression/test_set.txt` - 10 held-out pulses\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression/baseline_results.md` - frequency-only baseline\r\n- `experiments/cfi_compression/cfi_weighted_results.md` - CFI method results\r\n\r\n## Key Insights from This Session\r\n- CFI provides orthogonal signal to frequency (not a refinement)\r\n- Two types of persistence require different handling\r\n- Frequency-based compression treats both identically → loses research signal\r\n- CFI-weighted compression should preserve \"research trajectory\" invariants\r\n\r\n## Notes\r\n- Breakaway is stateless - each pulse is a fresh reconstruction\r\n- Gaps between sessions = compression, trust the files\r\n- Pulse script: active hours check DISABLED (authorized by Zach, 24/7 operation)\r\n```\r\nfile: research/CFI_RESULTS.md\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:27:46\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366176242}}
