{"type":"message","id":"1dcf8aa3","parentId":"3af92e31","timestamp":"2026-03-24T15:29:42.874Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_5fkr97oks6jy_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Pulse: 2026-03-24 112915\n\n## Applied Mutations\nJust applied: research/CFI_RESULTS.md (appended)\n\n\n## LLM Response\n<think>\r\nLet me analyze the current state and determine a concrete action that advances the goals.\r\n\r\nCurrent state:\r\n- Phase 0 and Phase 1 COMPLETE\r\n- CFI analysis done, finding that 44.8% of invariants are pure noise (CFI=0), only 5.7% have high CFI (>=0.7)\r\n- Key pending items:\r\n  - CFI-weighted compression experiment (compare vs frequency baseline)\r\n  - Implement CFI filtering to remove metaprogramming contamination\r\n  - Distinguish constant format vs research trajectory\r\n\r\nThe most actionable next step seems to be the CFI-weighted compression experiment. This would involve:\r\n1. Creating a comparison between frequency-based compression (current) vs CFI-weighted compression\r\n2. Testing next-pulse prediction quality\r\n\r\nI should write a concrete experiment script or document that advances this goal. Let me create a CFI-weighted compression experiment specification and/or a basic implementation.\r\n\r\nLooking at the goals, the most concrete next action would be to:\r\n- Create an experiment script that compares CFI-weighted vs frequency-based compression\r\n- Or implement CFI filtering\r\n\r\nLet me create a concrete experiment plan in a new file or update an existing one. I'll create an experiment specification that outlines how to test CFI-weighted compression.\r\n</think>\r\n\r\n### OBSERVATION\r\nThe CFI analysis reveals that only 5.7% of frequency-invariants are true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7), while 44.8% are pure metaprogramming noise (CFI=0). This suggests CFI-weighted compression could significantly outperform frequency-only compression for next-pulse prediction.\r\n\r\n### ACTION\r\nCreate `research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md` - a concrete experiment specification for comparing CFI-weighted compression against frequency-baseline, with pseudocode for implementation.\r\n\r\n### MUTATION\r\n```\r\nold_text: (new file)\r\nnew_text: # CFI-Weighted Compression Experiment\r\n**Created:** 2026-03-24\r\n**Status:** READY TO IMPLEMENT\r\n\r\n## Hypothesis\r\nCFI-weighted compression will produce better next-pulse prediction than frequency-only compression by filtering metaprogramming artifacts (CFI=0) and prioritizing true causal anchors (CFI>=0.7).\r\n\r\n## Experiment Design\r\n\r\n### Baseline: Frequency-Only Compression\r\n```python\r\ndef frequency_compress(invariants, top_k=100):\r\n    # Sort by frequency, keep top-k\r\n    sorted_inv = sorted(invariants, key=lambda x: x['freq'], reverse=True)\r\n    return sorted_inv[:top_k]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Experimental: CFI-Weighted Compression\r\n```python\r\ndef cfi_compress(invariants, top_k=100, cfi_threshold=0.7):\r\n    # Score = freq * CFI, filter CFI<threshold, keep top-k\r\n    scored = [(inv, inv['freq'] * inv['cfi']) for inv in invariants if inv['cfi'] >= cfi_threshold]\r\n    sorted_scored = sorted(scored, key=lambda x: x[1], reverse=True)\r\n    return [x[0] for x in sorted_scored[:top_k]]\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Prediction Quality Metric\r\n- Given compression output, predict next pulse content\r\n- Compare against actual next pulse (manual evaluation or overlap scoring)\r\n\r\n### Implementation Steps\r\n1. Extract frequency-invariants from `research/pulse_invariants.md` or equivalent\r\n2. Run both compression methods\r\n3. Generate \"predicted next pulse\" from each compressed set\r\n4. Score overlap with actual next pulse (pulse_2026-03-24_*.md)\r\n\r\n## Expected Outcome\r\nCFI-weighted compression will retain research trajectory content while discarding metaprogramming noise, yielding higher prediction fidelity.\r\nfile: research/CFI_COMPRESSION_EXPERIMENT.md\r\n```\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: 1\n- Completed at: 2026-03-24 11:29:35\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774366182871}}
